# 11_feature_tour_demo — auto-hide watch-mode showcase.
#
# Replaces the s191 universal-hide/show test in this slot. That test
# moved to tests/scripts/diagnostics/regression_universal_hide_show.curvzs
# where it lives as a structural regression. The "11" slot is now a
# pure watch-mode demo: turn on Auto-hide, crank Step delay to
# 300-500ms, hit Run, set Curvz down, and watch the app drive itself
# through a coordinated tour of its visible surface.
#
# What's on display:
#
#   1. Toolbar tool walk — five tools light up in sequence, the
#      left-side affordance changes with each, the radio invariant
#      holds throughout.
#   2. Grid on / style toggle / off — the canvas redraws every time
#      the grid lights up (Lines/Dots) and again when it disappears.
#      Most striking visual change in the whole tour.
#   3. Units walk — picks px, in, mm, pt in sequence. Every numeric
#      label around the canvas reformats. Cumulative effect: the
#      canvas is clearly reading the script's commands.
#   4. Margins on / off — printable-area box appears and vanishes.
#      Second-most-striking redraw after grid.
#   5. End on a clean state: Select tool active, grid + margins off,
#      px units. The next run lands in the same starting state.
#
# Captions ride along through `#[sub]` lines. With Step delay set
# (Scripter top toolbar) each caption sits visible on MainWindow's
# caption bar for 2x the delay before the next verb dispatches —
# reading speed at 300-500ms.
#
# Demo protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Set Step delay to ~400ms in the Scripter top toolbar.
#   3. Check Auto-hide (also in the Scripter top toolbar).
#   4. Click this script's row in the sidebar.
#   5. Hit Run. The Scripter hides; the tour plays on MainWindow.
#
# As a side effect, this script is a smoke test for the toolbar's
# radio invariant, the units dropdown's four options, and the
# Document-scope grid/margins enable switches. Every line should
# PASS at the end of the run.

#[sub] Welcome. A tour of Curvz, driven by script.

# Start from a known state. Select tool, no special view options.
tb_sel click
assert tb_sel active == true

#[sub] Five tools, clicking themselves on the toolbar.

tb_nod click
assert tb_nod active == true
assert tb_sel active == false

tb_pen click
assert tb_pen active == true
assert tb_nod active == false

tb_rec click
assert tb_rec active == true
assert tb_pen active == false

tb_ova click
assert tb_ova active == true
assert tb_rec active == false

tb_lin click
assert tb_lin active == true
assert tb_ova active == false

#[sub] Back to Select. Now watch the canvas itself.

tb_sel click
assert tb_sel active == true
assert tb_lin active == false

#[sub] Turn on the grid.

ins_grd_en set true
assert ins_grd_en active == true

#[sub] Switch grid style: lines, dots, lines again.

ins_grd_st pick "Dots"
assert ins_grd_st text == "Dots"

ins_grd_st pick "Lines"
assert ins_grd_st text == "Lines"

#[sub] Walk the units: pixels, inches, millimetres, points.

ins_can_un pick "px"
assert ins_can_un text == "px"

ins_can_un pick "in"
assert ins_can_un text == "in"

ins_can_un pick "mm"
assert ins_can_un text == "mm"

ins_can_un pick "pt"
assert ins_can_un text == "pt"

#[sub] Back to pixels.

ins_can_un pick "px"
assert ins_can_un text == "px"

#[sub] Grid off. Margins on.

ins_grd_en set false
assert ins_grd_en active == false

ins_mrg_en set true
assert ins_mrg_en active == true

#[sub] And margins off again.

ins_mrg_en set false
assert ins_mrg_en active == false

#[sub] Done. Clean state — Select tool, no grid, no margins, px.
